candide
=======

Something to quickly test (very) small c snippets.


What
----

candide is a bot in ##c on freenode, made by pragma-.

This script kinda mimics its behaviour.



Examples
--------

$ time candide <<< 'puts(getenv("HOME"));'
/home/izabera

real    0m0.075s
user    0m0.050s
sys     0m0.007s

$ candide
/* now we're entering text in a read -r -e
   emacs/vi keybindings work here */
int factorial(int n) {
  return n > 1 ? n * factorial(n-1) : 1;
}
main () {
  printf("%d\n",factorial(10));
}
                               /* press ^D */
3628800


Usage
-----

1. Run ./configure
2. Add candide to your PATH
3. Run candide

